messages.content: VideoSys-ComfyUI is a custom node for VideoSys, which is a tool developed by NUS-HPC-AI-Lab.
Where can I run VideoSys-ComfyUI online?
You can run VideoSys-ComfyUI online using the mirror site provided in the documentation.
Is there a tutorial available for VideoSys-ComfyUI?
Yes, there is a tutorial available for VideoSys-ComfyUI, as mentioned in the documentation.
What are the parameters used in the example provided for VideoSys-ComfyUI?
In the example provided for VideoSys-ComfyUI, the parameters used are: model_name (CogVideoX-2b), mode (low_mem), and prompt (Sunset over the sea).
What is the output of the example provided for VideoSys-ComfyUI?
The output of the example provided for VideoSys-ComfyUI is a video file with the source URL 'https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b69a5dab-8cd8-4733-bfd0-23dc6258defd'.
Can I use different models with VideoSys-ComfyUI?
The example provided uses the CogVideoX-2b model, but the documentation does not specify if other models can be used with VideoSys-ComfyUI.
Does VideoSys-ComfyUI support low memory mode?
Yes, the example provided shows that VideoSys-ComfyUI can be run in low memory mode (low_mem).
